EN: These two brackets can help prevent the cargo from sliding.
ZH: 11. 他喜欢在自己写的文章中使用斜杠来表示对话。
EN: He enjoys using slashes to represent dialogues in his own writing.
ZH: 12. 为了节省空间，他把衣柜从墙上拆下来，只留下了两根斜杠。
EN: To save space, he took the wardrobe off the wall, leaving only two brackets.
ZH: 13. 这个架子的稳固依赖于斜杠的质量。
EN: The stability of this shelf relies on the quality of the brackets.
ZH: 14. 我们需要一些额外的斜杠来加固这个支架。
EN: We need some extra brackets to reinforce this bracket.
ZH: 15. 衣柜的斜杠断了，导致衣物满地都是。
EN: The bracket of the wardrobe broke, causing clothes to be scattered all over the floor.
ZH: 16. 她用镊子扳动斜杠的两端，使其恢复原状。
EN: She used tweezers to bend the ends of the brackets and restore them to their original shape.
ZH: 17. 这个图书馆用斜杠来展示不同类别的书籍。
EN: This library uses brackets to display books of different categories.
ZH: 18. 他们从墙上挂了一根横置的斜杠，用来悬挂艺术品。
EN: They hung a horizontal bracket on the wall to display artworks.
ZH: 19. 这个装置需要四根斜杠来支撑整个结构。
EN: This device requires four brackets to support the entire structure.
ZH: 20. 工人们正在用螺丝固定斜杠和木板。
EN: The workers are using screws to secure the brackets and wooden planks.
